Sure, here are some example sentences that use the word "budna" in different forms and positions:

1. *Budna* sam cijelu noć razmišljala o tom problemu. (I was *awake* all night thinking about that problem.)
2. Prošli put sam prespavala predavanje, ali ovaj put ću biti *budna*. (Last time I slept through the lecture, but this time I'll be *awake*.)
3. Koliko *budno* pratiš vijesti? (How closely do you *follow* the news?)
4. Oni su *budni* i spremni za akciju u bilo koje vrijeme. (They are *alert* and ready for action at any time.)
5. Sestre su *budne* i rade zadaću, ali brat je zaspao. (The sisters are *awake* and doing their homework, but their brother has fallen asleep.)
6. *Budna* sam cijeli dan i trebam odmor. (I have been *awake* all day and need some rest.)
7. Čuvaj se! Moramo biti *budni* jer ne znamo što se može dogoditi. (Be careful! We need to *be alert* because we don't know what can happen.)
8. Ona je *budna* i svjesna svih okolnosti. (She is *awake* and aware of all the circumstances.)

Note: I have marked the word "budna" with an asterisk (*) in each sentence.